03/15/85 auto

Syntax as a command:  x auto mode


Function:  turns the automatic reboot mode on or off.  When auto reboot
mode is on, the system automatically takes a dump and (if possible)
reboots itself after a crash.  When auto reboot mode is off, the system
pauses in BCE awaiting operator action after a crash.


Arguments:
mode
   can be either "on" or "off".
